Diagnosis. Disc of pronotum smooth, polished, with small punctures in apical 1 / 4 , black. Elytra black, disc glabrous, striae largely effaced; apex laterally punctate ( Figs. 4 , 13 ). Rostral canal subglabrous. Aedeagus (
Figs. 41–42
) apically converging with straight sides. Transfer apparatus in dorsal view at middle strongly constricted.

Description. Holotype , male. Length. Pronotum + elytra: 4.3 mm . Color. Antenna ferruginous, rostrum and tarsi dark ferruginous; remainder black. Habitus subovate, in dorsal view almost without constriction between pronotum and elytra (
Fig. 4
); profile dorsally with shallow constriction between pronotum and elytron (
Fig. 13
). Rostrum 5.5 X as long as wide at base. Head. Vertex distinctly punctate.
